Package: vmavificient
Version: @VERSION@
Architecture: @ARCH@
Maintainer: VMAVIFICIENT contributors <noreply@example.invalid>
Section: video
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/matherose/VMAVIFICIENT
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.31)
Description: VMAF-aware AV1 encoder for HDR Blu-ray content
 vmavificient encodes UHD HDR Blu-ray sources to AV1 using
 SVT-AV1-HDR + libvmaf, with HDR10 mastering display + content
 light level passthrough, Dolby Vision profile 8.1 detection,
 in-process PGS subtitle OCR via Tesseract, and CRF search
 driven by VMAF targets per resolution.
 .
 Vendored third-party deps (SVT-AV1-HDR, FFmpeg, libvmaf, libopus,
 libdav1d, Tesseract, libcurl, openssl, etc.) are statically linked;
 only the glibc runtime is dynamic. The tessdata for English OCR
 is bundled at /usr/share/vmavificient/tessdata/.
